  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It would be nice if addresses could be replaced by \"name.eth\" with registered names at https://ens.domains/.\r\n\r\nMy thought would be to setup something like the following:\r\n) token = token.name.eth\r\n) During preICO:  contract = name.eth  (name.eth is set to the preICO contract address through the registrar)\r\n) After preICO: reset name.eth contract address at registrar to NULL contract (funds/tokens bounce back to sender)\r\n) At start of ICO: reset name.eth contract address at registrar to ICO contract \r\n\r\nI think this would allow upgrade of preICO/ICO contracts in middle of period by publishing a new contract and updating the name.eth address to the new contract address.\r\n\r\nOther address could be configured as well such as \"wallet.name.eth\".  Other features might be able to be added as well such as \"admin.name.eth\", \"banker.name.eth\", just a thought for the future as sub-domains addresses like this can be created.",
