    "body": "There is a good point here: https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/a/44440\r\nResolving the ens domain consumes gas. So I don't think it would be a good idea to change all our code here to receive domain names instead of addresses, it would be better to resolve them manually before the call. Or if you need to do it programmatically, you can add an intermediate contract that resolves the names and calls the openzeppelin contracts with the addresses.\r\n\r\nThe [ens docs](https://docs.ens.domains/en/latest/implementers.html#resolving-names-onchain) say that there are no libraries yet to resolve names on chain. So we could implement some here, but it sounds to me that those should leave on the ens project, not on openzeppelin. I wonder why they don't have this yet, I would have imagined that's one of the first things to do :man_shrugging: ",
